  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-01-28",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Abandoned Mine Land Area Redevelopment Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a credit for holders of qualified abandoned mine land area redevelopment bonds, as specified. Sets forth rules and formulae concerning the annual credit (including limits and carryover), the applicable credit rate, bond issuance and redemption, the amount of bonds designated, and a national volume cap.Includes the credit in gross income, to be treated as interest income. Permits the credit to be stripped (owner of bond different from person entitled to the credit). Treats the allowed credit as a payment of estimated tax. Permits the credit to be transferred. Limits the program to ten years from the issuance of the first qualified abandoned mine land area redevelopment bond."
  },
